description: From Ancient Greek διανοητικός (dianoētikós, “pertaining to thinking”), from διανοητός (dianoētós), verbal adjective of διανοέεσθαι (dianoéesthai, “to think”), from δια- (dia-, “through”) + νοέειν (noéein, “to think, suppose”).

adjectives.description: dianoetic (comparative more dianoetic, superlative most dianoetic)

entries.meaning: Pertaining to reason or thinking; intellectual.
